SIMPHIWE Mqedlana believes his son was murdered because he was an albino.His son&rsquo;s body was found in a shallow grave in Bizana, Eastern Cape on Thursday with his head, stomach and hand removed. The 56-year-old from Shayamoya in Kokstad, KZN, said his son, Esethu Jabula (28) had previously been reported missing to the police. &ldquo;I was worried about Esethu even before he went missing.&ldquo;I have read many stories about albinos being murdered,&rdquo; said the devastated dad. &ldquo;I even told him to be careful because some people think albinos&rsquo; body parts bring good luck.&ldquo;Seeing my son in that state was very painful, but I am relieved I will be able to bury him.&rdquo; He said he was planning to bury Esethu on 25 March as the cops had promised DNA tests would be done by then. KZN police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said the Eastern Cape police were investigating a case of murder.&ldquo;His body was found in the Eastern Cape. No one has been arrested,&rdquo; said Zwane.